  "text": "Kinetic Study in HLMs. Gemfibrozil (0.5-400 M) was preincubated with pooled HLMs (0.1 mg of protein/ml) at 37°C for 5 min in a final volume of 0.25 ml of Tris-HCl buffer (50 mM, pH 7.5) containing 8 mM MgCl 2 , and 25 g/ml alamethicin. The alamethicin concentration used in this study (25 g/ml) is that recommended by the supplier and is similar to that in a previous report [CITATION_1] . After preincubation of the reaction mixture, the reaction was started by adding UDP glucuronic acid to the mixture to a final concentration of 5 mM. After incubation at 37°C for 10 min, the reaction was terminated by precipitating the protein by adding 1.0 ml of acetonitrile. An internal standard [0.02 ml of deuterium gemfibrozil glucuronide (1 g/ml)] was then added, and the samples were centrifuged at 1870g for 10 min to obtain the supernatant, followed by evaporation of the supernatant to dryness using nitrogen gas. Samples were reconstituted in 0.2 ml of 0.1% formic acid/acetonitrile (6:4, v/v). Aliquots (30 l) were then injected into a highperformance liquid chromatography with tandem mass spectrometry system.",
